Comment:
There's not a Matthew Vaughn movie (that's not under a major studio) that I didn't like.  His tone has always been slightly tongue in cheek and not taking the whole business too seriously,  But he's never disrespected the medium either.  I sense that he really likes the magic of movie making.    Kingsman (the first one) was full of his trademark humor, flare, and clever use of music as part of a character.  Judging by this trailor, Kingsman 2 seems to be a joy ride (really, "Statesman" and "Kingsman", LOL!).  

Mr. Vaugh is producing and directing "I AM Pilgrim" now.   The book is one of my all time fave thrillers.  I think it is in good hands to have Vaughn attached to it.
